                     <interp inst="t18150405-109-person973" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am clerk to Mr. Bywaters, an upholsterer. Mr. Bywaters purchased woollen cloth of Mr. Gee; I received the cloth of Mr. Gee's porter. I paid 
               <persName id="t18150405-109-person974">
                  Robert 
                  Bruce
               <interp inst="t18150405-109-person974" type="surname" value="Bruce"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150405-109-person974" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150405-109-person974" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , the prisoner, fifty-six pounds six shillings, for the cloth, on the 28th of February, by my master's order, I paid him a check upon Messrs. Hammersley and Company, bankers; this is the check, it is signed by my master, and filled up by me; I paid it to 
               <persName id="t18150405-109-person975">
                  Robert 
                  Bruce
               <interp inst="t18150405-109-person975" type="surname" value="Bruce"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150405-109-person975" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150405-109-person975" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             for some drab cloth, he gave me a bill and receipt; this is the receipt.</p>
               <p>Mr. Adolphus. You did not go to the bankers with the prisoner at the time he presented the check - A. No.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. To Mr. Gee. The 28th of February was Tuesday, supposing he had received this on the Tuesday, when was it his duty to have brought it to account - A. It was his duty to have brought it to account immediately; we have a book; he ought to have entered it in the book paid, checks and bank notes are always put in the drawer; he never brought it to account.</p>
               <p>Q. Is your book here - A. No.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18150405-109-verdict591" type="verdictDescription">
